# A US national holiday celebrated on the second Monday in [[October]], for [[w:Christopher Columbus|Christopher Columbus]]' arrival in the Americas.

====Note====
In light of the recognition of the negative effects of European colonization on the indigenous populations of the Americas, many American states and cities have replaced Columbus Day with Indigenous Peoples' Day.

